    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-12-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-12-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="1019"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1019">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.9331/12–345: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Josselyn</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-12-03">December 3,
                            1945</date>.<lb/>[Received December 3—6:10 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>312. Situation regarding resumption export business now partially clarified and
                    local firms are beginning to apply for certification Consular invoices. (Mytel
                    237, November 20, 10 a.m.)</p>
                <p>… Would appreciate having instructions by radio regarding Consular
                    responsibilities, if any, in connection with shipments of goods which may have
                    been enemy owned or of enemy country origin …</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Josselyn</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
